# TrustVault - Data & AI Trust Platform

## What This Project Is

TrustVault is an enterprise-grade Data & AI Trust Platform built in Go. It acts as an active governance gateway between data sources and AI systems (RAG + LLMs). It classifies, governs, and audits all data flowing to/from AI.

## Architecture Summary

- **Language:** Go 1.22+ (single binary), Python/FastAPI (OCR sidecar only)
- **Metadata Backbone:** DataHub (GraphQL + OpenAPI) -- backend only, users NEVER see DataHub UI
- **Classification Model:** GLiNER ONNX (INT8, 197MB, runs on CPU, 60+ PII types, 4M chars/sec)
- **Document Processing:** PaddleOCR-VL (0.9B) for scanned PDFs/images
- **Vector DB:** Qdrant (managed) + external adapters
- **Message Broker:** Kafka (KRaft, no ZooKeeper)
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (multi-tenant, tenant_id on every table)
- **Auth:** JWT + API keys, full RBAC, super admin backdoor on :8099
- **Lineage:** OpenLineage events emitted to DataHub
- **LLM:** Agnostic proxy -- customer brings their own endpoint

## Code Philosophy: Less Code, More Features

- **6 internal packages only:** api, domain, store, events, external, pkg
- **Single binary:** `--mode=gateway` or `--mode=worker`
- **Generic CRUD[T]:** One repo handles all entities
- **Event-driven:** Side effects via event handlers, not inline calls
- **One models.go:** All DB models in one file with embedded TenantScoped

